# AutoMailer Frontend Documentation

## Overview
This document provides a comprehensive overview of the frontend architecture, UI components, and design system used in the AutoMailer application.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: React with TypeScript
- **Routing**: TanStack Router (file-based routing)
- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui (Radix UI primitives)
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS & Vanilla CSS (glassmorphism layer)
- **Visuals**: HTML5 Canvas (dynamic parallax particles)
- **Charts**: Recharts (gradient analytics area charts)
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **State Management**: React Context (AuthContext)
- **API Client**: Axios
- **Notifications**: Sonner
- **Animations**: Custom animation wrappers with TailwindCSS & CSS transitions

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── layout/
│   │   ├── DashboardShell.tsx      # Main layout wrapper for authenticated pages (contains canvas background layer)
│   │   ├── Sidebar.tsx             # Navigation sidebar with role-based menus and active sliding indicator
│   │   └── Topbar.tsx              # Header with user profile, theme toggle, and notification bell
│   ├── ui/                         # shadcn/ui components (46 components)
│   │   ├── dynamic-background.tsx  # Dynamic interactive canvas background with mouse parallax
│   │   ├── loading-skeleton.tsx    # Custom skeleton loaders
│   │   ├── empty-state.tsx         # Empty state components
│   │   └── animated-wrapper.tsx    # Animation wrapper components
│   └── StatCard.tsx                # Enhanced stat card component with hover gradient effects
├── lib/
│   ├── auth.tsx                    # Authentication context and logic
│   ├── admin-nav.ts                # Admin navigation menu
│   ├── sender-nav.ts               # Sender navigation menu
│   ├── theme.ts                    # Theme management (dark/light mode)
│   └── utils.ts                    # Utility functions (cn, etc.)
├── routes/
│   ├── landing.tsx                 # Landing page with AI personalization simulator widget
│   ├── login.tsx                   # Split-screen login page with quick-credential tiles
│   ├── onboarding.tsx              # SMTP onboarding stepper & documentation links
│   ├── _authenticated/             # Protected routes
│   │   ├── admin/                  # Admin dashboard pages (Recharts delivery volume stats, CSV workspace, settings)
│   │   ├── sender/                 # Sender pages (personalized composer workspace with token validation)
│   │   └── super-admin.tsx         # Super-admin page for platform statistics
│   └── index.tsx                   # Root route (redirects based on auth)
└── services/
    └── api.ts                      # Axios API client with typed endpoints & type-safe error boundaries
```

## Core Components

### Layout Components

#### DashboardShell
Main layout wrapper for authenticated pages.
- Props: `nav`, `navTitle`, `title`, `subtitle`, `children`
- Features: Responsive sidebar, topbar, main content area, integrated dynamic canvas background.
- Used by: All authenticated pages.

#### Sidebar
Navigation sidebar with role-based menus.
- Props: `items`, `title`
- Features: Active state highlighting, hover effects, system status indicator, active capsule sliding transition bar.
- Animations: Icon scale on hover, smooth translations.
- Styling: Transparent glassmorphic background, shadow effects.

#### Topbar
Header with user profile and actions.
- Props: `title`, `subtitle`
- Features: Avatar with initials, dropdown menu, theme toggle, logout, and notifications indicator.
- Styling: Transparent glassmorphic background, backdrop blur.

### UI Components

#### DynamicBackground
Renders multiple floating, colored orbs utilizing dynamic canvas radial gradients.
- Features: Responsive mouse move parallax (orbs gravitate toward the user's cursor with lerped easing).
- Theme Support: Automatically shifts to deeper colors (purple, indigo, sky blue) in dark mode, and soft pastel shades in light mode.

#### StatCard (Enhanced)
Enhanced statistics display card.
- Props: `label`, `value`, `hint`, `icon`, `trend`, `className`
- Features: Glassmorphic gradients, trend indicators (up/down), hover float scaling.
- Animations: Icon scale on hover, background gradient fade-in.
- Styling: Shadow effects, gradient text for values.

#### Loading Skeletons
Custom skeleton loaders for loading states.
- `StatCardSkeleton`: Skeleton for stat cards
- `TableSkeleton`: Skeleton for tables
- `CardSkeleton`: Skeleton for cards
- `Skeleton`: Base skeleton component

#### Empty States
Empty state components for no-data scenarios.
- `EmptyState`: Full empty state with action button
- `EmptyStateSimple`: Simple empty state without action
- Features: Icon support, customizable messaging

#### Animation Wrappers
Reusable animation components for smooth transitions.
- `FadeIn`: Fade-in animation
- `SlideIn`: Slide-in animation (supports direction: up/down/left/right)
- `ScaleIn`: Scale-in animation
- `Pulse`: Pulse animation
- `Bounce`: Bounce animation
- `Spin`: Spin animation

## Pages & Feature Workspaces

### Landing Page (`/landing`)
Modern showroom landing page.
- Features: Animated text gradients, floating statistics, dynamic canvas background, feature grids.
- **AI Personalization Simulator**: Interactive widget cycling through target leads (e.g. CEO, Founder) showing dynamic token replacement in template emails in real time.

### Login Page (`/login`)
Split-screen authentication page.
- Layout: Left glassmorphic credentials module, right feature banner.
- **Quick Demo Accounts**: Selectable grid tiles that automatically populate credentials for Super Admin, Admin, and Sender accounts.

### Onboarding Wizard (`/onboarding`)
SMTP configuration setup stepper.
- Features: Clear guide on how to generate and use Google App Passwords instead of raw passwords, complete with direct external links to security consoles.

### Admin Dashboard (`/admin`)
Admin campaign analytics overview.
- **Campaign Analytics Chart**: Embedded Recharts Area Chart displaying sent/delivered/opened email volumes over time with glowing filled gradients.
- **Outreach Quick Launch**: Interactive shortcut buttons for campaign creation.

### CSV Workspace (`/admin/csv`)
Side-by-side files manager.
- Features: File selection panel on the left, interactive lead spreadsheet view on the right.
- **AI Segmentation Scanner**: Triggers a glowing, backdrop-blurred scanning overlay when analyzing leads to simulate ML parsing.

### Senders & Logs Tables (`/admin/senders` and `/admin/logs`)
- Features: Glass tables with styled status badges, initials-based colored avatar badges, and search bars.

### Personalized Composer (`/sender/compose`)
Two-column advanced composition workspace.
- **Live Personalization Previewer**: Renders a formatted rendering of the email text where template tags (e.g. `{name}`) are swapped dynamically as the sender clicks through the list of assigned leads.
- **Syntax Tokenizer**: Parses email input in real-time, coloring correct variables in purple and warning about invalid variables (e.g., tags not present in the CSV) in glowing red.

## Design System & Styling

### Color Palette
- Primary: Vibrant violet/purple gradient accents.
- Background: Dynamic background canvas (deep dark-mode slate or soft light-mode tint).
- Card: Glassmorphic transparency with backdrop-blur (`16px`).
- Border: Semi-transparent borders with subtle white/dark highlight lines.

### Glassmorphism Class Utilities (`src/styles.css`)
- `.glass-panel`: Dynamic backdrop-blur (`16px`), saturated lighting overlay, and translucent borders.
- `.glass-input`: Focus-ring styling with scale transition.
- `.text-gradient-shine`: Gleaming text transitions.
- `.hover-float`: Elastic hover scaling.
- Custom styled scrollbars.

## API Integration & Error Boundaries
- **Axios Client**: Configured with a default interceptor adding token headers from localStorage.
- **Robust Type-Safety**: Extracted all explicit `any` catch block overrides. Implemented type-safe `unknown` error guards that fallback cleanly to generic error messages when Axios exceptions occur.

## Version
- Frontend: v2.1.0
- Last Updated: June 2026
